cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.MM

The paper proposes a deep convolutional neural network (CNN) model for automated quality grading in additive manufacturing (AM) process. This involves analyzing images of internal and surface defects in the layer-by-layer deposition of materials. Therefore, the most likely category is computer vision (cs.CV), followed by machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The proposed system also involves real-time monitoring and adjustment of parameters, which falls under robotics (cs.RO). Finally, the use of images and real-time monitoring suggests a possible connection to multimedia (cs.MM).
